ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Great statistic and computer programming introduction

Great class to give you a basic understanding of a number of statistical models. Yes, I'd recommend it. It provides one with a good grounding in the discipline and gives one the tools to be conversant with the bulk of quantitative research in sociology.
It is a great course to get a general sense of common statistical methods in sociology.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I rely on empirical work often; therefore, I need to be sufficiently competent in it

Statistical analysis is a huge part of sociology. One is lost without the basics and this course did a great job of conveying those. I am very appreciative of this class and thankful for what I've learned.
